        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How much does Triple Whale cost and is there a free alternative?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Triple Whale uses GMV-based pricing that scales with your store's revenue and chosen package, with a limited free plan. The free alternative for server-side tracking is CAPI Shield by Stack Architect, which provides server-side conversion events to Meta and Google Ads at $0 per month, typically reaching EMQ 7–8.5 — matching the attribution accuracy of Triple Whale's CAPI component." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is server-side tracking for Shopify and why does it matter in 2026?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Server-side tracking sends purchase events directly from your server to ad platforms like Meta and Google Ads, bypassing iOS privacy restrictions (ITP), Safari cookie expiry, ad blockers, and browser-based pixel limitations. Since iOS 14.5 ATT and continuing through iOS 26 Link Tracking Protection (which strips fbclid from Private Browsing, Mail, and Messages links), browser tracking has become increasingly unreliable. Server-side tracking recovers 20–40% of conversions that would otherwise go unmeasured. For Shopify stores running paid ads, it is now essential for accurate ROAS measurement." } },
