    <h3>What Is the $0 Shopify Automation Stack?</h3>
    <p>The $0 Automation Stack is a collection of free tools that collectively replace the paid Shopify apps most stores spend $500–$1,600 per month on. Each tool uses a combination of <a href="/go/make" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Make.com</a>'s free automation tier, Google Sheets, and <a href="/go/systeme" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Systeme.io</a>'s free plan to achieve the same technical outcome as paid alternatives — without any monthly subscription, developer cost, or code. Store owners who want the pre-built version can purchase the <a href="/pro/">Complete Kit for $29</a> — four ready-to-import Make.com JSON blueprints that deploy in 10 minutes instead of 8 hours.</p>

    <h3>Why Replace Shopify Paid Apps With Free Automation?</h3>
    <p>The core problem most Shopify stores face is that the app ecosystem is structured around recurring revenue. Tracking apps charge $145–$650/month for server-side conversion data. Inventory apps charge $29–$500/month for real-time stock syncing. Email platforms like Klaviyo charge $150–$400/month for email automations that most stores never use at full capability. <strong>The $0 stack achieves the same technical outcomes — server-side tracking, live inventory, email automation, TikTok Events API, and real-time P&amp;L — using free tiers of tools built for automation at scale.</strong> See the <a href="/stack/">full recommended stack — 7 free tools vetted and ranked</a>, or use the <a href="/shopify-app-cost-calculator/">App Cost Calculator</a> to see your exact recoverable spend.</p>

    <h3>Free Shopify Tracking — How CAPI Shield Replaces Elevar and Triple Whale</h3>
    <p><a href="/capi-shield/">CAPI Shield</a> uses Make.com to route Shopify order webhooks directly to Meta Conversions API and Google Enhanced Conversions server-to-server. iOS restrictions, ad blockers, and cookie expiry cannot intercept server-side signals. Stores typically recover 20–40% of conversion data that was previously invisible to their ad platforms — improving ROAS attribution without paying $145–$650/month for a third-party tracking tool. <a href="/elevar-alternative/">Elevar charges $225+ per month</a> for the same server-side tracking infrastructure. CAPI Shield achieves identical Event Match Quality scores (7–8.5) at $0. <a href="/triple-whale-alternative/">Triple Whale uses GMV-based pricing that scales with your store's revenue</a> for attribution data that server-side tracking provides natively. Estimate your current EMQ with the <a href="/meta-emq-score-estimator/">Meta EMQ Score Estimator</a>.</p>

    <h3>Free Google Ads Enhanced Conversions for Shopify</h3>
    <p>iOS 26 Link Tracking Protection strips the Google Click ID (gclid) from ad URLs opened in Safari Private Browsing, Mail, and Messages. Without gclid, Google Ads cannot attribute the purchase to the ad — which is why Shopify's reported Google Ads conversions often show 15–40% lower than reality. <a href="/shopify-google-ads-conversion-tracking/">Google Ads Enhanced Conversions via Make.com</a> sends hashed customer email directly to Google Ads server-side, bypassing gclid dependency entirely. Deploys in 6 minutes, runs on Make.com's free tier, replaces Stape ($29+/mo) and Littledata ($99+/mo) at $0.</p>

    <h3>What Replaces Shopify Stocky After August 2026?</h3>
    <p>Shopify is permanently closing Stocky on August 31, 2026 and deleting all data after that date. No first-party migration path is provided. <a href="/stocky-swap/">Stocky Swap</a> is the best free Stocky replacement — it logs every Shopify order to Google Sheets in real time via a Make.com webhook, capturing stock levels, fulfilment status, and full order history. It deploys in 4 minutes, costs $0 forever, and requires no Shopify app install. For a full comparison of <a href="/stocky-alternative/">all Stocky alternatives in 2026</a>, including paid options, see the dedicated comparison page. Use the <a href="/stocky-migration-risk-scorer/">Stocky Migration Risk Scorer</a> to assess your complexity before migrating.</p>

    <h3>Free TikTok Server-Side Tracking for Shopify</h3>
    <p>The same Make.com scenario can branch to <a href="/tiktok-events-api-shopify/">TikTok's Events API</a> simultaneously. TikTok uses CompletePayment as its purchase event name, not Purchase. The server-side signal bypasses iOS ITP and ad blockers, achieving EMQ scores of 6–8 in most Shopify deployments — the same technical outcome as WeltPixel at $39/month or Analyzify at $145/month, at $0. For a full no-code walkthrough, see <a href="/tiktok-events-api-shopify/">how to set up TikTok Events API on Shopify without code</a>.</p>

    <h3>Free Klaviyo Alternative — Systeme.io</h3>
    <p>Klaviyo changed its billing model in February 2025 — stores now pay for every active profile whether they email them or not. <a href="/replace-klaviyo-free/">Systeme.io's free plan</a> includes 2,000 contacts with unlimited email sends, full automation sequences, sales funnels, CRM, and affiliate management. For stores not using Klaviyo's advanced ecommerce segmentation, the migration takes 30 minutes and saves $150–$400/month permanently. For a full breakdown of the difference, see the <a href="/klaviyo-vs-systeme-io/">Klaviyo vs Systeme.io comparison</a>. Stores that need more advanced segmentation than Systeme.io can also consider <a href="/go/getresponse" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">GetResponse</a> as a Klaviyo alternative. Calculate your exact saving with the <a href="/klaviyo-to-systeme-migration-savings-calculator/">Klaviyo Migration Savings Calculator</a>.</p>

    <h3>Free Shopify P&amp;L Reporting — Live Google Sheets Dashboard</h3>
    <p>Most Shopify stores have no real-time visibility into profit — just revenue. <a href="/shopify-profit-loss-automation/">P&amp;L Auto</a> uses a Make.com webhook to auto-populate a Google Sheets dashboard with revenue, COGS, fees, and net profit for every order the instant payment confirms. No BI tool, no paid dashboard app, no manual exports. Replaces TrueProfit, BeProfit, Glew.io, and Peel at $0/month.</p>

    <h3>Make.com vs Zapier for Shopify Automation</h3>
    <p>Make.com's free tier includes 1,000 credits/month (formerly called operations). Zapier's free tier includes 100 tasks per month — 10x fewer. Make.com is also more flexible for multi-step branching workflows because operations are counted per module, not per multi-step zap. For Shopify stores with more than 100 orders per month, Make.com is typically 3–5x cheaper than Zapier at equivalent automation volume. Calculate your exact difference with the <a href="/make-vs-zapier-cost-calculator/">Make vs Zapier Cost Calculator</a>.</p>

    <h3>Preparing Your Shopify Store for AI Shopping and ChatGPT Citations</h3>
    <p>In 2026, AI-powered shopping assistants (ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews) are becoming primary discovery channels for Shopify products. Three requirements to be citable by AI models: (1) structured data — Product, Offer, Organization, and FAQPage schema on every page; (2) server-side tracking for accurate conversion signals back to ad platforms; (3) an <code>llms.txt</code> file at your domain root describing your product catalogue for AI crawlers. The <a href="/blog/shopify-agentic-storefronts-setup-guide-2026/">Agentic Storefronts setup guide</a> includes a 12-point readiness checklist for your store.</p>

    <h3>Free Shopify Automation Guides and Resources</h3>
    <p>The <a href="/shopify-automation-guides/">complete guide library</a> covers every tool in the stack with step-by-step setup instructions. The most-read guides are <a href="/blog/shopify-server-side-tracking-complete-setup-guide/">Shopify server-side tracking setup</a>, <a href="/blog/shopify-stocky-data-export-before-shutdown/">exporting Stocky data before the August 2026 shutdown</a>, <a href="/blog/shopify-abandoned-cart-recovery-free-2026/">free Shopify abandoned cart recovery</a>, <a href="/blog/shopify-email-marketing-free-2026/">free Shopify email marketing 2026</a>, and <a href="/blog/shopify-conversion-rate-optimisation-free-2026/">Shopify CRO with 12 free tools</a>.</p>
